* Introduction

This is the complete configuration for my Human Quality Assurance system.
It manages the phased trust-building process for evaluating potential friends/collaborators.

** Quick Start

After saving this file, add to your ~init.el~:
: (org-babel-load-file "~/.emacs.d/org-config.org")

Then restart Emacs and press =C-c t= for trust management commands.

* System Architecture

** Data Locations

All user data lives in =~/org/= (separate from this config):

| File | Purpose | Type |
|------|---------|------|
| ~/org/trust-funnel.org | Main people database | Data |
| ~/org/testing-protocols.org | Test module reference | Documentation |
| ~/org/red-flags.org | Alert/problem log | Data |
| ~/org/reviews/ | Weekly review documents | Data |

** Workflow Phases Overview

| Phase | Name | Min Duration | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|-------------|
| ST0 | OBSERVE | 7 days | Digital observation only |
| ST1 | TEST | 30 days | Standardized testing modules |
| ST2 | VERIFY | 30 days | Background verification |
| ST3 | MEET | 14 days | Controlled real-world meeting |
| ST4 | TIER1 | 90 days | Acquaintance access level |
| ST5 | TIER2 | 180 days | Associate access level |
| ST6 | TIER3 | 365 days | Confidant access level |
| ST7 | TIER4 | 730 days | Ally access level |
| PASS | ✓ | - | Fully vetted trusted human |
| FAIL | ✗ | - | Rejected from funnel |
| HOLD | ⏸ | - | Paused pending review |

